<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 23 at 8:42PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A LINE OF SHOWERS WILL AFFECT
ROCKINGHAM...WESTERN PITTSYLVANIA...EASTERN HENRY AND SOUTHEASTERN
FRANKLIN COUNTIES...THE CITY OF DANVILLE AND THE CITY OF
MARTINSVILLE...
At 841 PM EDT, radar indicated showers with heavy rains were located
along a line extending from Leatherwood to near Intelligence.
Movement was northeast at 25 mph.
Winds in excess of 40 mph are possible with these showers.
Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Eden...
Reidsville...
Martinsville...
Wentworth...
Mayodan...
and Madison.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these showers, and may
cause localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</description>
